road and playful. Several times his arms blur into multiple outlines, emphasizing fast animated motion. The plain background keeps the focus on him and the product.\n\nHe moves closer to the television, leaning forward with clasped hands, then reaching toward the set’s controls. He stretches one arm toward the front panel and touches or indicates one of the round knobs beneath the screen. He also reaches toward the edge or top of the television, then pulls back into another proud, upright pose. The TV continues showing the same three people inside the screen while the animated man performs beside it, sometimes crouching low, sometimes springing up with his arms high.\n\nAround the middle of the commercial, a second animated figure enters from the right. This character is shorter and stockier, also male-presenting, with a long nose, small bow tie, dark suit, and very short legs. He approaches the television from the right side while the tall man remains to the left. The shorter man reaches toward the set’s control area. As he stands near the knobs, the TV screen goes blank, losing the image of the three performers. The tall character places a hand on or near the top of the television and looks down toward the smaller figure, as if giving him space to demonstrate or speak.\n\nThe shorter character walks in front of the television and then further left, coming into clearer view while the tall character towers behind him near the set. The tall figure stands with one hand raised beside his head and the other hand on his chest, watching. The smaller figure faces forward with a serious, slightly worried or earnest expression. He gestures with both hands, then touches his head as if thinking. He appears to address the audience directly, standing in the foreground while the television remains to his right and the tall presenter’s long legs and torso loom behind him.\n\nThe shorter figure then opens or pulls at the front of his dark suit jacket, revealing large lettering on his shirt or chest area that reads “Muntz TV.” The words are bold and centered on his torso, making the brand name visually explicit. He holds this display briefly, then lets the jacket close again and clasps his hands in front of him. Afterward, he turns and walks back toward the television, passing beneath or in front of the tall man’s long body.\n\nThe smaller character returns to the set and again handles the control knob area on the front. He stands to the right of the television with one hand near a round knob. The screen, which had been blank, lights up again and the same image of three people reappears inside the rounded screen. The shorter figure pauses beside the TV, then moves away toward the right edge, while the tall animated man resumes his animated dance on the left.\n\nWith the television picture restored, the tall presenter takes over visually again. He dances beside the set, bending low with his coat tails flaring like wings, then rising with his arms thrown wide. He leans in toward the TV as if admiring the picture, places hands on his belly and chest, points upward, and swings his arms in sweeping motions. The TV remains on the right, steadily displaying the three people on its screen. The tall figure’s long nose, bow tie, and black jacket tails remain prominent as he bounces and glides across the plain background.\n\nNear the end, the tall character continues his exuberant motions, raising both fists high with a wide open-mouthed expression, then settling back down. The television picture begins to darken; the image of the three performers becomes dim and then disappears into a dark screen. The tall man’s energy drops abruptly. He stands to the left of the now-dark television, arms hanging down and body slack, as if the performance has concluded. He bends forward, and the upper part of his body or coat transforms visually into a sign-like surface with the words “Muntz TV” written prominently across it. The final image holds this brand name on the